This role pays in the range of $110-130K per year and the final salary will be determined by experience and skills. 
Job Summary: 
The Test Automation Architect is a technical hands-on leader in the testing organization and is a strategic participant across many development efforts. As a Test Architect, you are passionate about driving efficiency in the software development process by using leading tools and frameworks to deliver complete automated test suites and provide test automation architecture to a large global insurance organization. This position could also be referred to as a Software Engineer in Test (SDET). The Test Architect provides overall leadership on test strategy, script design, script execution, automation framework, service virtualization, data virtualization, and environment design & advanced Test Management strategies all combined to improve effectiveness, costs and velocity. Responsible for the design, enhancement and future growth of test automation architecture and framework.
 Key Responsibilities: Provide leadership around test techniques or methodologies to support complex or strategic direction for creation of the automation test suite environment 
ÔÇß Provide leadership in the execution of automated test scripts and validation of requirements 
ÔÇß Lead the design, modification, development, and implementation of test automation architecture and framework 
ÔÇß Responsible for the automation architecture and provides direction on automation techniques. Responsible for the research and implementation of the advanced features of test automation 
ÔÇß In an agile/scrum environment, may: 
ÔÇß Execute practical application of Agile framework components (user stories, scrum, sprints, etc.). 
ÔÇß Participate in Scrum, Daily Stand-up, Sprint and iterative development activities ‚Äì prepared to take on any role within the Agile team 
ÔÇß For activities related to Test Management, may: 
ÔÇß Provide consultation on the most complex testing strategies 
ÔÇß Contribute and provide subject matter expertise to iterative test strategy 
ÔÇß Provide subject matter expertise on framework direction and output 
ÔÇß Extend tool capabilities and integrate with other technologies by coding interfaces, new functions, custom objects, etc. 
ÔÇß Execute test cases within the Functional, Mobile, Performance or Web Services Automation framework 
ÔÇß Create, consult and maintain an environment where a Test Driven Development behavior is fostered 
ÔÇß Create and validate automated scripts that support Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery pipeline 
ÔÇß Consult and provide direction on test environment issues; act as SME for external environment team communications 
ÔÇß Apply Testing Lifecycle Management principles in the context of a product 
ÔÇß Possess technical competency and takes on leadership role to interact with application developers to ensure software quality 
